C++

int -  4 bytes - 32 bits - max size ~ 2^31-1 ~= 10^9

long long int - 8 bytes - 64 bits - max size ~ 2^64-1 ~= 10^18

So, the maximum length of integers that can be stored using C++ datatypes
cannot exceed 18 digits

If N> 10^18, it is considered a big integer.

Possible solutions - store big integer in array or as strings